   3:src/cpp_runtime.cpp **** 
   4:src/cpp_runtime.cpp **** // PDF p.10: the global operator new/delete must be implemented as wrappers
   5:src/cpp_runtime.cpp **** // around mem_alloc/mem_free, so all C++ dynamic allocation in user code
   6:src/cpp_runtime.cpp **** // flows through the syscall.
   7:src/cpp_runtime.cpp **** //
   8:src/cpp_runtime.cpp **** // We define every overload the linker is likely to want (scalar, array,
   9:src/cpp_runtime.cpp **** // sized C++14 forms) so that any user-code shape compiles.
  10:src/cpp_runtime.cpp **** //
  11:src/cpp_runtime.cpp **** // NOTE: kernel code must NEVER use `new` — that would mean the kernel
  12:src/cpp_runtime.cpp **** // calling its own syscall. Kernel internals use MemoryAllocator::alloc
  13:src/cpp_runtime.cpp **** // directly + placement-new for construction.
